{"QUICA":[{"def":"A small South American opossum (Didelphys quica), native of Guiana and Brazil.","pos":""}],"QUICH":[{"def":"He could not move nor quich at all.","pos":""}],"QUICHUAN":[{"def":"Designating, or pertaining to, a linguistic stock of South American Indians, including the majority of the civilized tribes of the ancient Peruvian Empire with some wild tribes never subjugated by the Incas.","pos":""}],"QUICK":[{"def":"Alive; living; animate; -- opposed to dead or inanimate.","pos":""},{"def":"Characterized by life or liveliness; animated; sprightly; agile; brisk; ready.","pos":""}],"QUICK-SIGHTED":[{"def":"Having quick sight or acute discernment; quick to see or to discern.","pos":""}],"QUICK-WITTED":[{"def":"Having ready wit Shak.","pos":""}],"QUICK-WITTEDNESS":[{"def":"Readiness of wit.","pos":""}],"QUICKBEAM":[{"def":"See Quicken tree.","pos":""}],"QUICKEN":[{"def":"To shorten the radius of (a curve); to make (a curve) sharper; as, to quicken the sheer, that is, to make its curve more pronounced.","pos":""}],"QUICKEN TREE":[{"def":"The European rowan tree; -- called also quickbeam, and quickenbeam.","pos":""}],"QUICKENER":[{"def":"One who, or that which, quickens.","pos":""}],"QUICKENING":[{"def":"The first motion of the fetus in the womb felt by the mother, occurring usually about the middle of the term of pregnancy.","pos":""}],"QUICKLIME":[{"def":"Calcium oxide; unslacked lime; -- so called because when wet it develops great heat.","pos":""}],"QUICKLY":[{"def":"Speedily; with haste or celerity; soon; without delay; quick.","pos":""}],"QUICKNESS":[{"def":"The condition or quality of being quick or living; life.","pos":""},{"def":"Activity; briskness; especially, rapidity of motion; speed; celerity; as, quickness of wit.","pos":""}],"QUICKSAND":[{"def":"Sand easily moved or readily yielding to pressure; especially, a deep mass of loose or moving sand mixed with water, sometimes found at the mouth of a river or along some coasts, and very dangerous, from the difficulty of extricating a person who begins sinking into it.","pos":""}],"QUICKSET":[{"def":"A living plant set to grow, esp.","pos":""}],"QUICKSILVER":[{"def":"The metal mercury; -- so called from its resemblance to liquid silver.","pos":""}],"QUICKSILVERED":[{"def":"Overlaid with quicksilver, or with an amalgam of quicksilver and tinfoil.","pos":""}],"QUICKSILVERING":[{"def":"The mercury and foil on the back of a looking-glass.","pos":""}],"QUICKSTEP":[{"def":"A lively, spirited march; also, a lively style of dancing.","pos":""}]}